#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/hpc-howto.xml:50
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Gentoo Linux, a special flavor of Linux that can be automatically optimized\n"
"and customized for just about any application or need. Extreme performance,\n"
"configurability and a top-notch user and developer community are all hallmarks\n"
"of the Gentoo experience.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/hpc-howto.xml:57
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Thanks to a technology called Portage, Gentoo Linux can become an ideal secure\n"
"server, development workstation, professional desktop, gaming system, embedded\n"
"solution or... a High Performance Computing system. Because of its\n"
"near-unlimited adaptability, we call Gentoo Linux a metadistribution.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/hpc-howto.xml:64
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"This document explains how to turn a Gentoo system into a High Performance\n"
"Computing system. Step by step, it explains what packages one may want to\n"
"install and helps configure them.\n"
