#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/hpc-howto.xml:804
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Message passing is a paradigm used widely on certain classes of parallel\n"
"machines, especially those with distributed memory. MPICH is a freely\n"
"available, portable implementation of MPI, the Standard for message-passing\n"
"libraries.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/hpc-howto.xml:811
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"The mpich ebuild provided by Adelie Linux allows for two USE flags:\n"
"<e>doc</e> and <e>crypt</e>. <e>doc</e> will cause documentation to be\n"
"installed, while <e>crypt</e> will configure MPICH to use <c>ssh</c> instead\n"
"of <c>rsh</c>.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/hpc-howto.xml:817
#, no-wrap
msgid "Installing the mpich application"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/hpc-howto.xml:818
#, no-wrap
msgid "# <i>emerge -a mpich</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/hpc-howto.xml:822
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"You may need to export a mpich work directory to all your slave nodes in\n"
"<path>/etc/exports</path>:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/hpc-howto.xml:827
#, no-wrap
msgid "/home  *(rw)\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/hpc-howto.xml:831
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Most massively parallel processors (MPPs) provide a way to start a program on\n"
"a requested number of processors; <c>mpirun</c> makes use of the appropriate\n"
"command whenever possible. In contrast, workstation clusters require that each\n"
"process in a parallel job be started individually, though programs to help\n"
"start these processes exist. Because workstation clusters are not already\n"
"organized as an MPP, additional information is required to make use of them.\n"
"Mpich should be installed with a list of participating workstations in the\n"
"file <path>machines.LINUX</path> in the directory\n"
"<path>/usr/share/mpich/</path>. This file is used by <c>mpirun</c> to choose\n"
"processors to run on.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/hpc-howto.xml:844
#, no-wrap
msgid "Edit this file to reflect your cluster-lan configuration:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/hpc-howto.xml:847
#, no-wrap
msgid "/usr/share/mpich/machines.LINUX"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/hpc-howto.xml:848
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"# Change this file to contain the machines that you want to use\n"
"# to run MPI jobs on. The format is one host name per line, with either\n"
"#    hostname\n"
"# or\n"
"#    hostname:n\n"
"# where n is the number of processors in an SMP. The hostname should\n"
"# be the same as the result from the command \"hostname\"\n"
"master\n"
"node01\n"
"node02\n"
"# node03\n"
"# node04\n"
"# ...\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/hpc-howto.xml:864
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Use the script <c>tstmachines</c> in <path>/usr/sbin/</path> to ensure that\n"
"you can use all of the machines that you have listed. This script performs\n"
"an <c>rsh</c> and a short directory listing; this tests that you both have\n"
"access to the node and that a program in the current directory is visible on\n"
"the remote node. If there are any problems, they will be listed. These\n"
"problems must be fixed before proceeding.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/hpc-howto.xml:873
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"The only argument to <c>tstmachines</c> is the name of the architecture; this\n"
"is the same name as the extension on the machines file. For example, the\n"
"following tests that a program in the current directory can be executed by\n"
"all of the machines in the LINUX machines list.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/hpc-howto.xml:879
#, no-wrap
msgid "Running a test"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/hpc-howto.xml:880
#, no-wrap
msgid "# <i>/usr/local/mpich/sbin/tstmachines LINUX</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><note>
#: en/hpc-howto.xml:884
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"This program is silent if all is well; if you want to see what it is doing,\n"
"use the -v (for verbose) argument:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/hpc-howto.xml:888
#, no-wrap
msgid "Running a test verbosively"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
